title: Cheetah Deaths Mar India’s Efforts to Reintroduce the Big Cats
description: The animals had been extinct for more than 70 years in the country, which has just begun a program that brought 20 cheetahs from Africa to a wildlife sanctuary.

title: In a Sharp Reversal, Biden Opens a Path for Ukraine to Get Fighter Jets
description: The president told allied leaders that he would allow Ukrainian pilots to be trained on American-made F-16s, and is prepared to approve other countries’ transferring the jets to Ukraine.

title: Canada Wildfires Rage in Alberta and British Columbia
description: Wildfires raging in Alberta and British Columbia have created a sense of panic and fear, and forced thousands of residents to evacuate from their homes.

title: Ukraine arrests a top judge as the country’s corruption scandal grows.
Russia says its defense minister visited the Zaporizhzhia area of southern Ukraine.
Russia Targets Kyiv for 10th Time This Month
description: The attacks come as a widely anticipated Ukrainian counteroffensive looms.

title: Tensions Flare in Georgia as Direct Flights Resume With Russia
description: Moscow also eased visa requirements for Georgians. But its actions have stirred fears in Georgia, which was invaded by Russia in 2008.

title: U.S. Diplomats in Sudan Shredded Passports, Stranding Sudanese
description: Officials destroyed Sudanese passports on security grounds as they evacuated the Khartoum embassy. Now the passport owners are trapped in a war zone.

title: Why the Leaders of Turkey and Thailand Have an Interest in Elections
description: Turkey and Thailand held two huge elections this week, both with uncertain outcomes. Each shows some of the benefits that elections can hold for leaders who have amassed power with the tools of the state.

title: 95-Year-Old Australian Woman Is Tasered by Police
description: She was holding a knife, but weighs 95 pounds and uses a walker. The episode, which took place in a care facility, prompted outrage, questions and a police investigation.

title: 1923: Germany Seizes French Plane
description: Paris claimed a violation of the Treaty of Versailles after the German authorities impounded an aircraft that been forced to land outside Nuremberg because of engine trouble.

title: Floods in Northern Italy Kill at Least 14
description: At least 14 people have died and thousands more were left homeless after some areas received half their annual rainfall in 36 hours.

title: Liz Truss, Britain’s Briefest Prime Minister, Meets Taiwan’s Leader
description: Liz Truss, the former British prime minister, met Taiwan’s leader, who has sought to push back against China’s efforts to isolate the island democracy.

title: Zelensky Is Expected to Attend G7 Summit, Part of New Diplomatic Tour
description: The Ukrainian leader’s expected appearance at the G7 in Japan would come after a visit to Saudi Arabia, where he arrived on Friday for talks with Arab leaders.

title: Averting a Debt Limit Crisis
description: Both parties seem more willing to compromise on the debt limit.

title: Zelensky Attends Arab League Summit in Saudi Arabia
description: Mr. Zelensky said he had landed in Saudi Arabia and will meet with the kingdom’s leader, Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, and others.

title: How Hillsong, a Hip Megachurch, Became Entangled in Scandal
description: A new documentary series explores the history of Hillsong, known for its celebrity congregants and fashionable trappings before being struck by a series of scandals.

title: He Promised Change in Thailand. But Will He Be Allowed to Lead?
description: Pita Limjaroenrat led his party to victory in the Thai election and seems poised to become the next prime minister, unless the military blocks him.

title: Rockets Sent Israelis Running From the Beach. A Rare Seal Brought Them Back.
description: The incongruous arrival of a large and endangered monk seal has distracted Israelis from a period of violence and political unrest.

title: A South Korean Poet’s Work Honors Cats
description: The South Korean writer Hwang In-suk feeds stray cats on late-night walks through Seoul. The routine informs her poems about loneliness and impermanence.

title: G7 Countries Borrow China’s Economic Strategy
description: Wealthy democracies rev up an effort to spend trillions on a new climate-friendly energy economy, while stealing away some of China’s manufacturing power.

title: Biden Pays Silent Tribute to Victims of Hiroshima Bomb
description: The president joined other leaders in laying wreaths at a memorial to the first wartime use of a nuclear weapon, amid growing fears that one could be used again.

title: Video Shows Greece Abandoning Migrants at Sea
description: Video evidence shows asylum seekers, among them young children, being rounded up, taken to sea and abandoned on a raft by the Greek Coast Guard.

title: Tsunami Warning After Earthquake in South Pacific
description: Waves as high as three feet could hit Vanuatu, the U.S. tsunami warning system said, after a 7.7 magnitude earthquake was recorded near New Caledonia.

title: We Want to Hear From Australia Letter Readers
description: What should we be covering? Are there stories that the rest of the world should know about? Let us know.

title: Your Friday Briefing
description: Negotiations over the U.S. debt limit.

title: Zelensky to Attend G7 Meeting in Japan
description: President Volodymyr Zelensky of Ukraine was preparing to make the audacious trip halfway around the world as his country moves toward a counteroffensive against Russian forces.

title: How the G7 Oil Price Cap Has Helped Choke Revenue to Russia
description: Group of 7 leaders are prepared to celebrate the results of a novel effort to stabilize global oil markets and punish Moscow.
